| colspan="5" align=left | [[Maria Callas]] (1923â1977), American-born [[Greeks|Greek]] [[soprano|operatic soprano]], was the preeminent [[prima donna]] (lead female opera singer) of her day, and the first modern soprano to revive forgotten operas of the 19th-century [[bel canto]] repertoire. Callas revolutionized opera performances through her vocal and dramatic intensity, transforming what had traditionally been empty display pieces into serious and emotion-filled dramas.
